00374     uint64_t bank_assign                  : 3;  /**< Port assignment for each memory bank. Memory structure is 64k words * 246 data bits (plus
00375                                                          ECC). This is further divided into 64 banks each containing 1k words * 246 data bits. A
00376                                                          bank can only support one access per cycle, this is implemented by assigning each bank to
00377                                                          a specific requester. Most requesters can only make one request per cycle so that mostly
00378                                                          solves the problem. RWC is the only requester that can make multiple requests per cycle
00379                                                          and will need to implement its own bank-aware scheduler to prevent bank conflicts. Bank
00380                                                          assignment can be reconfigured dynamically, but memory accesses to a bank must be quiesced
00381                                                          before that bank can be reassigned to another requester. A host request can access any
00382                                                          bank; arbitration logic will prevent bank conflicts for host requests.
00383                                                          Addresses: bit<15:10> = bank, bit<9:0> = offset.
00384                                                          Bank 0 corresponds to memory address 0x0000-0x03FF.
00385                                                          Bank 1 corresponds to memory address 0x0400-0x07FF.
00386                                                          Bank 63 corresponds to memory address 0xFC00-0xFFFF.
00387                                                          See OSM_BANK_ASSIGN_E for encoding. */
